== Military flags ==

=== Rank flags used in all branches of the Armed Forces ===
Originally used only by the Navy, the use of these rank flags was extended in 2005 to all branches of the Armed Forces by an amendment to the relevant ministerial ordinance.<ref>{{pl icon}} [http://www.abc.com.pl/serwis/mp/2005/1165.htm Zarz<U+0105>dzenie Ministra Obrony Narodowej z dnia 14 grudnia 2005 r. zmieniaj<U+0105>ce zarz<U+0105>dzenie w sprawie szczeg<U+00F3><U+0142>owych zasad u<U+017C>ywania znak<U+00F3>w Si<U+0142> Zbrojnych Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej oraz ustalenia innych znak<U+00F3>w u<U+017C>ywanych w Si<U+0142>ach Zbrojnych Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej] (Ordinance of the Minister of National Defence amending the Ordinance on Detailed Rules for the Use of the Insignia of the Armed Forces of the Republic of Poland and Establishment of other Insignia Used in the Armed Forces of the Republic of Poland, [[14 December]] [[2005]]), Monitor Polski z 2005 r. Nr 82 poz. 1165</ref> They are flown to mark the presence and pay respect to the highest civilian and military authorities: the [[President of the Republic of Poland]] who is ''ex officio'' the [[commander-in-chief]] of the Armed Forces; the Minister of National Defence who acts on the commander-in-chief's behalf in peacetime; [[Marshal of Poland]], the highest rank in the Polish army (no living holders [[as of 2007]]); and the Chief of the [[General Staff of the Polish Armed Forces|General Staff]].

